            Plot outline                                          
                                                                  
            As hard-hitting as its title, Brute Force was         
            the first of Jules Dassins forays into the           
            crime genre, a prison melodrama that takes a          
            critical look at American society as well.            
            Burt Lancaster is the timeworn Joe Collins,           
            who, along with his fellow inmates, lives             
            under the heavy thumb of the sadistic, power-         
            tripping guard Captain Munsey (a riveting             
                Hume Cronyn). Only Collinss dreams of escape             
            keep him going, but how can he possibly bust          
            out of Munseys chains?
